     The xxxxeeeeuuuuccccaaaa window is divided vertically into two sub-windows:


     *    The left sub-window (also called the files window) con-
          tains  a  list  of icons corresponding to the files and
          directories present in the current directory.  The icon
          varies  depending  upon  the  type of files (e.g. LOTOS
          programs,  C  programs,  Labelled  Transition  Systems,
          directories, ...) have different icons.

          Clicking on a directory icon makes the  current  direc-
          tory  to  change and to enter this directory. Following
          the usual convention, the  parent  directory  is  named
          "..".

          Clicking on a file icon displays a menu  that  proposes
          all  operations  available  for this file. This menu is
          "contextual" in the sense that the list  of  operations
          proposed  in  the  menu  depends upon the type of file.
          Selecting  an  operation  in  the  menu  launches   the
          corresponding  EUCALYPTUS  tool(s).  To click on a file
          icon, any mouse button can be used and all buttons have



